<paragraph id="8BB136AAFF9DFFD5FF32FB81BE7DBA8D" blockId="11.[92,1047,1027,1307]" pageId="11" pageNumber="136">
This is the largest of the series and is only reliably known from the 
<typeStatus id="54B58808FF9DFFD5FC2FFB86BF93BA6B" box="[921,970,1028,1052]" pageId="11" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
series. It is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D29FF9DFFD5FE1EFBA6BE6CBA4C" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1924" box="[424,565,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Exoprosopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevinasis">
<emphasis id="B97AEAB8FF9DFFD5FE1EFBA6BE6CBA4C" box="[424,565,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="136">E. brevinasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D29FF9DFFD5FDD8FBA6BF4EBA4C" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1924" box="[622,791,1060,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Exoprosopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnipennis">
<emphasis id="B97AEAB8FF9DFFD5FDD8FBA6BF4EBA4C" box="[622,791,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="136">E. magnipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which may sometimes approach it in size. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5BFF9DFFD5FEF2FBC1BD8FBA2C" author="BEZZI, M." box="[324,470,1091,1115]" pageId="11" pageNumber="136" refId="ref11358" refString="BEZZI, M., 1924, The Bombyliidae of the Ethiopian Region. (London: British Museum, Natural History), 390 pp." type="book" year="1924">Bezzi (1924)</bibRefCitation>
states that there are no white scale bands on the abdomen. However, this is not correct. The specimens are greasy but all have at least traces of bands on all terga, except the ®rst, as in these other species. However, the abdomen is very short and broad and the terga are swollen, as noted by Bezzi, giving the specimens a distinctive appearance. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5BFF9DFFD5FD7BFB41BF07BAAC" author="BEZZI, M." box="[717,862,1219,1243]" pageId="11" pageNumber="136" refId="ref11358" refString="BEZZI, M., 1924, The Bombyliidae of the Ethiopian Region. (London: British Museum, Natural History), 390 pp." type="book" year="1924">Bezzi (1924)</bibRefCitation>
provided a full description and illustration of the wing.
</paragraph>
